TY  - JOUR
T1  - Monetarism, Rational Expectations, Oligopolistic Pricing, and the MPS Econometric Model
AU  - McCallum, Bennett T.
Y1  - 1979/02/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/260739
DO  - 10.1086/260739
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 57
EP  - 73
VL  - 87
IS  - 1
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - This paper investigates the conjecture that oligopolistic pricing behavior will invalidate the Lucas-Sargent policy-ineffectiveness proposition even if expectations are formed rationally. The procedure is to examine the properties of an analytical macroeconomic model that incorporates a simplified version of the MPS wage-price sector. It is shown that the validity of the conjecture depends upon the precise manner in which lags are built into the price adjustment equation. A crucial condition is isolated and used to motivate an empirical test. The results, based on quarterly U.S. data, are predominantly consistent with the ineffectiveness proposition.
AB  - This paper investigates the conjecture that oligopolistic pricing behavior will invalidate the Lucas-Sargent policy-ineffectiveness proposition even if expectations are formed rationally. The procedure is to examine the properties of an analytical macroeconomic model that incorporates a simplified version of the MPS wage-price sector. It is shown that the validity of the conjecture depends upon the precise manner in which lags are built into the price adjustment equation. A crucial condition is isolated and used to motivate an empirical test. The results, based on quarterly U.S. data, are predominantly consistent with the ineffectiveness proposition.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/260739
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/260739
Y2  - 2024/03/22
