TY  - JOUR
T1  - On the Specification of Asset Equilibrium in Macroeconomic Models: A Note
AU  - Karni, Edi
Y1  - 1979/02/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/260745
DO  - 10.1086/260745
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 171
EP  - 177
VL  - 87
IS  - 1
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - This paper describes two alternative institutional setups for trading in assets and goods. One setup corresponds to a "beginning-of-period:" asset equilibrium specification; the other suggests both beginning and end-of-period equilibrium. It is shown that: (a) each model is internally consistent and the two models are consistent with each another; (b) the two models abide by Walra's law and in neither of them is there a need for a separate "balance-sheet constraint"; and (c) the continuous time version of the two models is well defined.
AB  - This paper describes two alternative institutional setups for trading in assets and goods. One setup corresponds to a "beginning-of-period:" asset equilibrium specification; the other suggests both beginning and end-of-period equilibrium. It is shown that: (a) each model is internally consistent and the two models are consistent with each another; (b) the two models abide by Walra's law and in neither of them is there a need for a separate "balance-sheet constraint"; and (c) the continuous time version of the two models is well defined.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/260745
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/260745
Y2  - 2024/03/22
